'''''Star Wars Summer Special'' 1985''' was a comic book released in the United Kingdom that reprinted a number of Star Wars stories, including the stories published in the US as [[Star Wars (1977) 24|''Star Wars'' (1977) 24]] and [[Star Wars (1977) 29|''Star Wars'' (1977) 29]]. The cover features a portion of the cover art from that original issue. The stories were first published in the UK in issues of ''[[Star Wars Weekly]]''. According to an advertisement first published inside [[Return of the Jedi Weekly 111|''Return of the Jedi Weekly'' 111]] and later issues, it was scheluded to be released on "end of june", alongside other summer specials like ''A-Team'', ''Masters of the Universe'', ''Doctor Who'', ''Transformers'' and ''Spiderman''.

Also included is a story titled ''[[R2-D2's tales from the Data Banks]]'', which just reprints a non-''Star Wars'' short story from Marvel Comics' ''Tales to Astonish'' #42, titled "I Am Not Human!"

